"GROUP BY" statements groups rows that have the same values. Used with- COUNT(), MAX(), 
 MIN(), SUM(), AVG() to group the result.
"ORDER BY" statements orders rows based on the given condition. 

SYNTAX:
a. 
SELECT COUNT(column_name_1), column_name_2
FROM table_name
GROUP BY column_name;
ORDER BY column_name_4;

Example:
SELECT COUNT(customerID), customerName
FROM Customers
GROUP BY countryName
ORDER BY countryName ASC; 

NOTE: ASC | DESC denotes ascending | descending order.